==English==

===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From Latin [[heros]] ← Homeric Greek [[ἥρως]] (demi-god), according to Platon derives from [[Eros]].

===Noun===
[[Category:English irregular plurals]]
{{en-noun|hero|heroes}}

#A [[real]] or [[mythical]] [[person]] of [[great]] [[bravery]] who carries out [[extraordinary]] [[deed]]s.
#A [[role model]].
#The main [[protagonist]] in a work of fiction.
#A [[champion]].
#A large sandwich made from meats and cheeses.

====Synonyms====
*see [[WikiSaurus:hero]]

